Depends on how you're running Linux- are you starting X?  If no (which I
believe is your case), then you'd need to run OS/2 without the Presentation
Manager (the graphic stuff).  That would pretty much get rid of any reason
to convert. If yes, then it depends on what you load.  Get rid of
multimedia, deregister all the classes that you don't need or use, and you
might get close.  But it's hard to compare, because the functionality is
different...
